{"title_page": "Government General Degree College, Dantan-II", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox university |\n  name           = Government General Degree College, Dantan-II |\n  established    = 2015|\n  type           = Undergr|\n  citi | \n  state          = [[West Bengal]]|\n  country        = [[India]] |\n  coordinates = {{coord|21|57|51.06|N|87|28|40.51|E|display=inline,title}}|\n  campus         = Rural|\n  affiliations   = [[Vidyasagar University]] |\n  website        =  {{URL|http://www.dantan2govtcollege.ac.in}}\n|}}\n[[File:Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II (2).jpg|alt= Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II, Paschim Medinipur, West Bengal, India|thumb|Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II, Paschinipur, West Bengal, India]]\n'''Government General Degree College,  Dantan-II''', also known as '''Kashmuli Government College''',<ref name=UGC>[http://www.ugc.ac.in/inside/browse_reco_colleges.php?st=West%20Bengal Colleges in West Bengal, University Grants Commission] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111116042454/http://www.ugc.ac.in/inside/browse_reco_colleges.php?st=West+Bengal |date=2011-11-16 }}</ref> is the government degree college in [[Paschim Medinipur district]]. This college began its journey in 2015, with the objective of spreading quality higher education in one of the backward blocks in the district of Paschim Medinipur.  It offers undergraduate courses in arts and science. It is affiliated to [[Vidyasagar University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Affiliated College of Vidyasagar University | url=http://vidyasagar.ac.in/academics/AffiliatedColleges.aspx|}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nThe college is located at Kashmuli in Danton II block, one of the remote corner of Paschim Medinipur district of Westbengal, India. The nearest Municipality area is Egra which is 10&nbsp;km away and the nearest town [[Kharagpur]] is 54&nbsp;km away. The distance of the college from [[Kolkata]] is about 180&nbsp;km.\n\n== Courses offered ==\n* B.A. Honours in Bengali, English, History, Philosophy, Political Science,\n* B.SC. Honours in Physics,Chemistry and Mathematics.\n* B.A. General in Bengali, English, History, Philosophy, Political Science,\n* B.SC. General in  Physics,Chemistry and Mathematics\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Vidyasagar University}}\n\n[[Category:Colleges affiliated to Vidyasagar University]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Paschim Medinipur district]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in India]]\n\n\n{{WestBengal-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox university |\n  name           = Government General Degree College, Dantan-II |\n  established    = 2015|\n  type           = Undergraduate college|\n  city           = Kashmuli | \n  state          = [[West Bengal]]|\n  country        = [[India]] |\n  coordinates = {{coord|21|57|51.06|N|87|28|40.51|E|display=inline,title}}|\n  campus         = Rural|\n  affiliations   = [[Vidyasagar University]] |\n  website        =  {{URL|http://www.dantan2govtcollege.ac.in}}\n|}}\n[[File:Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II (2).jpg|alt= Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II, Paschim Medinipur, West Bengal, India|thumb|Government General Degree College, Kashmuli, Dantan-II, Paschim Medinipur, West Bengal, India]]\n'''Government General Degree College,  Dantan-II''', also known as '''Kashmuli Government College''',<ref name=UGC>[http://www.ugc.ac.in/inside/browse_reco_colleges.php?st=West%20Bengal Colleges in West Bengal, University Grants Commission] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111116042454/http://www.ugc.ac.in/inside/browse_reco_colleges.php?st=West+Bengal |date=2011-11-16 }}</ref> is the government degree college in [[Paschim Medinipur district]]. This college began its journey in 2015, with the objective of spreading quality higher education in one of the backward blocks in the district of Paschim Medinipur.  It offers undergraduate courses in arts and science. It is affiliated to [[Vidyasagar University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Affiliated College of Vidyasagar University | url=http://vidyasagar.ac.in/academics/AffiliatedColleges.aspx|}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nThe college is located at Kashmuli in Danton II block, one of the remote corner of Paschim Medinipur district of Westbengal, India. The nearest Municipality area is Egra which is 10&nbsp;km away and the nearest town [[Kharagpur]] is 54&nbsp;km away. The distance of the college from [[Kolkata]] is about 180&nbsp;km.\n\n== Courses offered ==\n* B.A. Honours in Bengali, English, History, Philosophy, Political Science,\n* B.SC. Honours in Physics,Chemistry and Mathematics.\n* B.A. General in Bengali, English, History, Philosophy, Political Science,\n* B.SC. General in  Physics,Chemistry and Mathematics\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Vidyasagar University}}\n\n[[Category:Colleges affiliated to Vidyasagar University]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Paschim Medinipur district]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in India]]\n\n\n{{WestBengal-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2409:4061:2e10:60be:bb80:e9e9:ba19:fd9b", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_General_Degree_College,_Dantan-II"}
{"title_page": "2018 Winter Olympics opening ceremony", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox news event\n| title           = 2018 Winter Olympics<br />opening ceremony\n| image_name      = Opening ceremony DVo-tC7U0AAPyz3.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = [[Yuna Kim]], South Korean Olympic figure skating champion, lights the Olympic cauldron\n| date            = {{start date|df=yes|2018|02|09}}\n| time            = 20:00 \u2013 22:20 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]] ([[UTC+09:00|UTC+9]])\n| place           = [[Pyeongchang]], [[South Korea]]\n| coordinates     = {{coord|37|40|03|N|128|42|20|E|region:KR-42_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| also known as   = Peace in Motion\n| filmed by       = [[Olympic Broadcasting Services|OBS]] on behalf of [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|footage={{youtube|u7eiNnw6Kwc|PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony}}\n| participants    = \n| awards          = \n| url             = \n}}\n{{2018 Winter Olympics}}\n\nThe '''[[Olympic opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2018 Winter Olympics]]''' was held at the [[Pyeongchang Olympic Stadium]] in [[Pyeongchang]], [[South Korea]] on 9 February 2018. It began at 20:00 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]] and finished at approximately 22:20 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]]. The Games were officially opened by [[President of the Republic of Korea]] [[Moon Jae-in]].\n\n==Preparations==\nThe site of the opening ceremony, [[Pyeongchang Olympic Stadium]], was built specifically for the Games. The pentagonal stadium seated 35,000. The organizers for the event said the shape was chosen because it is a combination of different shapes, a circle, a square, and a triangle, which represent heaven, earth, and mankind.<ref name=\"npr\" /><ref>https://abcnews.go.com/International/olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-peace-motion-kick-off/story?id=52930433</ref> No Olympic or Paralympic events were be held at the stadium, which was only used for the opening and closing ceremonies. The venue was torn down afterwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.citylab.com/life/2018/02/its-time-for-the-pop-up-olympics/552896/|title=It's Time for the Pop-Up Olympics|last1=Eaton|first1=Joe|date=February 9, 2018|publisher=CITYLAB|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe broadcast of the Opening Ceremony of the 2018 Winter Olympic Games was available in more than 200 countries around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://2018winterolympicswiki.com/opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-2018-live-9-february-2018/917/|title=Pyeongchang 2018 Opening Ceremony LIVE on 9 February 2018|date=18 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref> \n*[[Ha Hyun-woo]] of the band [[Guckkasten]], [[Ahn Ji-young]] of the musical duo [[Bolbbalgan4]], [[Lee Eun-mi (singer)|Lee Eun-mi]] and [[Jeon In-kwon]] with his band Deulgukhwa performed and sang John Lennon's \"[[Imagine (John Lennon song)|Imagine]]\" at the opening ceremony.<ref name=\"PerformatOpening\">{{cite news|last1=Hong|first1=C.|title=Ha Hyun Woo, Bolbbalgan4\u2019s Ahn Ji Young, And More To Perform At Olympics Opening Ceremony|url=https://www.soompi.com/2018/01/30/ha-hyun-woo-bolbbalgan4s-ahn-ji-young-perform-2018-pyeongchang-olympics-opening-ceremony/|accessdate=1 February 2018|work=[[Soompi]]|publisher=[[Viki (website)|Viki, Inc.]]|date=30 January 2018}}</ref>\n*The Rainbow Children's Choir performed an arrangement, with Korean traditional musical instruments, of the national anthem, \u201c[[Aegukga]]\u201d.<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\">{{Cite web | title = Who Were the Singers at the Opening Ceremony of the Winter Olympics? | last = Garcia | first = Maira | work = nytimes.com | date = 10 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-11 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/10/arts/music/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-singers.html | quote =  }}</ref> The multiethnic children's choir was formed to educate the Korean public about multicultural families living in Korea.<ref>https://www.sbnation.com/2018/2/9/16979556/olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live-results-events-highlights</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/10/arts/music/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-singers.html|title=Who Were the Singers at the Opening Ceremony of the Winter Olympics?|last=Garcia|first=Maira|date=10 Feb 2018|website=PyeongChang 2018|access-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Insooni]] sang the theme song for the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Torch Relay, \"Let Everyone Shine\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BSyw06cGlJ8|title=(ENG) Theme song for the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Torch Relay (ENG sub)|first=|last=PyeongChang 2018|date=21 September 2017|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>https://www.olympicchannel.com/en/video/detail/opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-2018-replays/</ref>\n\n==Ceremony==\nThe ceremony's message centered on peace, passion, harmony, and convergence.<ref name=\"npr\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetorch/2018/02/09/584368072/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-welcomes-the-world|title=Winter Olympics Opening Ceremony: Pyeongchang Welcomes The World|publisher=NPR|last1=Chappell|first1=Bill|date=February 9, 2018|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>https://www.businessinsider.com/2018-winter-olympics-the-best-photos-from-the-opening-ceremony-2018-2</ref>\n\nFive children from rural Gangwon province led the ceremony, which included one [[Inmyeonjo]] (a mythical creature with a body of a bird and a head of a human, a creature that only appears when the world is at peace), [[Four Symbols (China)|four mythical creatures]], including a white tiger \u2014 spirit animal protector of Korea and the mascot of these Games, natural floral and fauna, and a cast of 2,000. Five children were used to symbolize the five Olympic rings, and the five names were chosen to represent fire, water, wood, metal, and earth, the five elements that are believed to make up the Earth.<ref name=\"npr\" /><ref>https://www.olympic.org/news/pyeongchang-opening-ceremony-celebrates-culture</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/09/sports/olympics/opening-ceremony.html</ref>\n\n[[Augmented reality]] and [[5G]] technology were also incorporated in the event. The largest drone show in history, featuring 1,218 [[Shooting Star (drone)|Shooting Star drones]], was planned for the ceremony but cancelled at the last minute; television audiences were shown a version that had been recorded the previous December.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/olympics-opening-ceremony-drone-show/|title=Inside the Olympics Opening Ceremony World-Record Drone Show|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-02-09|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Banks|first1=Paul M.|title=Winter Olympics Verify Mike Pence Hypocrisy on NFL National Anthem Protests|url=http://www.chicagonow.com/patriotic-dissenter/2018/02/winter-olympics-verify-mike-pence-hypocrisy-on-nfl-national-anthem-protests/|accessdate=13 February 2018|work=[[ChicagoNow]]|date=9 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring the opening ceremony the organizing committee was a victim of a cyber attack, but without major consequences.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Meeks|first1=David|title=By not standing for Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics, VP Mike Pence embarrassed America|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/winter-olympics-2018/2018/02/12/vice-president-mike-pence-north-korea-embarrassed-america/328254002/|accessdate=13 February 2018|work=[[USA Today]]|date=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Programme==\n===Parade of Nations===\n{{main|2018 Winter Olympics Parade of Nations}}\nThe Parade of Nations was led, according to custom due to hosting the original [[ancient Olympics]], by the Greek team, followed by other competing countries in alphabetical order based on their names in the [[Korean language]], with the host country, South Korea, concluding the march.<ref name=\"Guardian\" />\n\nThe delegations from both the host nation [[South Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics|South Korea]] and [[North Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics|North Korea]] ([[Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics]]) marched under the [[Korean unification flag]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/feb/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live |title=Winter Olympics 2018 opening ceremony \u2013 live!|date=9 February 2018|work=Guardian|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> South Korean [[Won Yun-jong]] and North Korean [[Hwang Chung-gum]] both held the flagpole.<ref name=\"tele\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2018/02/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-review-pyeongchang-unites/|title=Winter Olympics 2018 opening ceremony review: Pyeongchang unites the world in a blizzard of emotion and effects|publisher=The Telegraph|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Pence1\">{{cite news|last1=Radnofsky|first1=Louise|last2=Cheng|first2=Jonathan|title=Pence Sat During Opening Ceremony. Some Koreans Took Offense.|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/pence-sat-during-opening-ceremony-some-koreans-took-offense-1518259101|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nEven though the temperature in the stadium during the ceremony was very cold, Bermuda's delegation wore shorts and Tongan [[Pita Taufatofua]] repeated his shirtless and oiled up [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|Summer Olympic appearance]].<ref name=\"tele\" />\n\nBackground music for the parade began with an instrumental version of \"[[Hand in Hand (Olympic theme song)|Hand in Hand]]\" by [[Koreana (band)|Koreana]] and included modern dance remixes of songs such as \"\ub2e8\ubc1c\uba38\ub9ac\" by [[Cho Yong-pil]] and of traditional Korean music, as well as the following [[K-pop]] hits:  \"[[Gangnam Style]]\" by [[Psy]], \"[[Likey]]\" by [[Twice (band)|Twice]], \"[[Fantastic Baby]]\" by [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]], \"[[DNA (BTS song)|DNA]]\" by [[BTS (band)|BTS]], and \"[[Red Flavor]]\" by [[Red Velvet (band)|Red Velvet]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=6 December 2017|title=2018 Winter Olympics Kick Off With Korean Stars PSY & BTS During Opening Ceremonies|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8098906/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-psy-bts-skating-oasis-ed-sheeran|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> \"Red Flavor\" was cut off just as the unified Korean team was introduced.\n\n===Torch lighting===\n{{see also|2018 Winter Olympics torch relay}}\n[[File:PyeongChang 2018 Cauldron.jpg|thumb|right|Cauldron]]\n\nThe Olympic flame was on a 101-day relay across South Korea. The start of the ceremony takes place in Olympia of Greece. Apostles Angelis, 24 years old cross-country skier, is selected to be the first torchbearer. He said \"It is a great honour for me to be chosen as the first torchbearer for the Olympic Winter Games of 2018. It is truly a unique moment that I am looking forward to. I feel very proud and with a unique sense of happiness.\" <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/olympia-awaits-flame-lighting-ceremony-for-pyeongchang-2018|title=Olympia Awaits Flame Lighting Ceremony for PyeongChang 2018|last=|first=|date=19 October 2017|website=Olympic Games|access-date=}}</ref> Park Ji-Sung, football player in Republic of Korea, was the second person to hold the torch. After the flame touring around Greece for a week, it reached the Acropolis on 30th of October. <ref name=\":0\" /> There were 36 ceremonies held in different cities over a week, then the flame arrived to the PyeongChang Panathenaic Stadium. More than 500 torchbearers participated to follow the rituals of Olympic cycle, and carried the message of peace.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/information-to-the-media-pyeongchang-2018-olympic-flame-lighting-ceremony|title=Information to the Media - PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Flame-Lighting Ceremony|last=|first=|date=23 October 2017|website=Olympic Games|access-date=}}</ref> In the stadium, Opera soloist [[Sumi Hwang]] sang the [[Olympic anthem]] during the torch lighting ceremony. The final person to hold the torch was [[Inbee Park]], the golfer from Republic of Korea. [[Jong Su-hyon]] from North Korea and [[Park Jong-ah]] from South Korea carried the torch and headed up stairs toward the cauldron. <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/09/sports/olympics/opening-ceremony.html|title=Winter Olympics 2018 Opening Ceremony: Highlights and Analysis|last=Keh|first=Andrew|date=9 Feb 2018|website=PyeongChang 2018|access-date=}}</ref>As the torch neared the cauldron, an ice skating rink with South Korean figure skater [[Yuna Kim]] was revealed.<ref name=\"tele\" /> Yuna Kim is the well-known figure skater who won gold medal in 2010 and silver medal in 2014.<ref name=\":1\" /> The cauldron was designed to represent a full moon when it is not lit. Kim received the torch and lit the cauldron.<ref name=\"npr\" />\n\n===Wish Fire===\n\nThe final segment entitled \"Wish Fire\" featured Korean dance group Just Jerk<ref>[https://www.pyeongchang2018.com/en/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-pyeongchang-2018-opening-ceremony Behind the Scenes of the PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony]</ref> (who became known internationally for their participation in the [[America's Got Talent (season 12)|twelfth season]] of ''[[America's Got Talent]]'') entered the stage dressed as [[Dokkaebi]], and performers with sparklers on roller blades. This segment in total featured 2,000 fireworks within and out of the stadium, some reaching as high as {{convert|1,300|m|ft}}.<ref name=\"npr\" />\n\n=== Intel\u00ae Drone Light Show ===\nMore than 1,200 Intel [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs)]] or drones flying above PyeongChang to celebrate the opening of 2018 Winter Olympic Games. Intel\u00ae drone team now holds the Guinness World Record of flying largest number of drones. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/sports/olympic-games/drones.html|title=Intel\u00ae Drones at The Olympic Games|last=|first=|date=|website=intel\u00ae|access-date=}}</ref> The drones flew together to form custom animations illustrating snow boarding, skiing, other different sports, as well as the [[Olympic symbols|iconic Olympic rings]]. The Shooting Star drones carried on the symbol of unity and progress from lighting of the torch. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/technology-innovation/aerial-technology-light-show.html|title=A Record-Breaking Show at PyeongChang 2018|last=|first=|date=2018|website=intel\u00ae|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===Russian hacking===\nOn 24 February, the ''[[Washington Post]]'' reported that U.S. intelligence uncovered [[Russia]]n spies hacked computers during the Opening Ceremony, an act that was previously speculated to be the work of North Korea. Analysts believed the Russians instigated the February 9 attack as a way to retaliate for the International Olympic Committee's decision to restrict the participation of Russian athletes in the 2018 Winter Olympics as punishment for doping violations.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/winter-olympics-2018/2018/02/25/winter-olympics-russian-spies-hacked-opening-ceremony-report/371051002/ Report: Russian spies behind Winter Olympics cyber attack]. ''US Today''. Retrieved 26 February 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.cnet.com/news/russian-spies-reportedly-hacked-winter-olympics-2018-washington-post/ Russian spies reportedly hacked Winter Olympics]. ''CNET''.  Retrieved 26 February 2018.</ref>\n\n==Dignitaries in attendance==\n[[File:Vice President Pence's Trip to Asia (28394490479).jpg|thumb|[[Mike Pence]], [[Vice President of the United States]]. With [[Moon Jae-in]], [[Thomas Bach]] and [[Kim Yo-jong]]]]\n\nAbout 25 heads of state attended the ceremony, in addition to the [[UN]] Secretary General. [[President of Russia]] [[Vladimir Putin]] was invited to attend, but declined due to the ban on Russian athletes by the [[IOC]].\n\n* {{flagicon|Finland}} [[Finland]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Juha Sipila]]\n* {{flagicon|France}} [[France]] - [[President (government title)|President]] [[Emmanuel Macron]], [[Ministry of Europe and Foreign Affairs|Minister of Europe and Foreign Affairs]] [[Jean-Yves Le Drian]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/politics/diplomacy/825180.html|title=\ud3c9\ucc3d \uc624\ub294 \uc678\uad6d\uc815\uc0c1 \ubc8c\uc368 15\uba85\u2026\u2018\uc62c\ub9bc\ud53d \uc678\uad50\u2019 \uaf43\ud53c\uc6b4\ub2e4|date=26 December 2017|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref> and [[Minister of Youth Affairs and Sports (France)|Minister of Sports]] [[Laura Flessel-Colovic|Laura Flessel]]\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} [[Canada]] - [[Governor General of Canada|Governor General]] [[Julie Payette]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/governor-general-payette-south-korea-olympics-1.4507777|title=Gov. Gen. Julie Payette to attend opening of winter Olympics|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"guard\" />\n* {{flagicon|China}} [[China]] - [[Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China|Politburo standing]] member [[Han Zheng]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bta.bg/en/gallery/image/4683766|title=SOUTH KOREA-CHINA-HAN ZHENG-WINTER OLYMPICS-OPENING CEREMONY|date=February 9, 2018|access-date=February 10, 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Colombia}} [[Colombia]] - [[Vice President of Colombia|Vice President]] [[\u00d3scar Naranjo]]<ref name=\"guard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/feb/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live|title=Winter Olympics opening ceremony: Koreans enter under unified flag \u2013 as it happened|publisher=The Guardian|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Denmark]] - [[Crown Prince]] [[Frederick, Crown Prince of Denmark|Frederick]]\n* {{flagicon|Estonia}} [[Estonia]] - [[President of Estonia|President]] [[Kersti Kaljulaid]]<ref name=\"koreanetKaljulaid\">{{cite news|authorlink1=Kim Tae Won and Kim Young Shin|title=Korea-Estonia summit to help launch peace through Olympics|url=http://www.korea.net/NewsFocus/policies/view?articleId=153762|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=Korea.net|date=7 February 2018|quote=President Moon Jae-in held a meeting with President Kersti Kaljulaid of Estonia who is on a visit to Korea to attend the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Germany}} [[Germany]] - [[President of Germany|President]] [[Frank-Walter Steinmeier]]<ref name=\"dwspanishgermanypres\">{{cite news|title=Presidente de Alemania apoya di\u00e1logo entre Coreas|url=http://www.dw.com/es/presidente-de-alemania-apoya-di%C3%A1logo-entre-coreas/a-42531385|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=spanish}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Italy]] - Sports Minister of [[Italy]] Luca Lotti<ref name=\"lastampalotti\">{{cite news|author=Daniela Cotto|title=Il ministro Lotti a Casa Italia, l\u2019incontro con Lindsey Vonn|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2018/02/09/sport/speciali/olimpiadi-pyeongchang-2018/il-ministro-lotti-a-casa-italia-lincontro-con-lindsey-vonn-AqQhOx28jG9DmCvFllo2zL/pagina.html|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=La Stampa|date=9 February 2018|language=italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210153105/http://www.lastampa.it/2018/02/09/sport/speciali/olimpiadi-pyeongchang-2018/il-ministro-lotti-a-casa-italia-lincontro-con-lindsey-vonn-AqQhOx28jG9DmCvFllo2zL/pagina.html|archive-date=10 February 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Japan}} [[Japan]] - [[Prime Minister of Japan|Prime Minister]] [[Shinzo Abe]]<ref name=\"abeatolympicsnhkworldspa\">{{cite news|title=Mandatarios de Jap\u00f3n y Corea del Sur acuerdan continuar ejerciendo presi\u00f3n sobre Corea del Norte|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/es/news/58224/|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[NHK World]]|language=Spanish|quote=Abe y Moon sostuvieron una reuni\u00f3n de aproximadamente una hora en un hotel cerca del Estadio Ol\u00edmpico de Pyeongchang antes de asistir el viernes a la ceremonia de apertura de los Juegos Ol\u00edmpicos de Invierno.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211072236/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/es/news/58224/|archive-date=11 February 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|South Korea}} [[South Korea]] - [[President of South Korea]] [[Moon Jae-in]]<ref name=\"LaVanguardiaMoon\">{{cite news|title=L\u00edo de protocolo ante la inauguraci\u00f3n de los juegos de invierno de Pyeongchang|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/internacional/20180209/44637116639/juegos-olimpicos-de-invierno-2018.html|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=La Vanguardia|language=spanish}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Latvia}} [[Latvia]] - [[President of Latvia|President]] [[Andris Berzins]]\n* {{flagicon|Lithuania}} [[Lithuania]] - [[President of Lithuania|President]] [[Dalia Grybauskait\u0117]]<ref name=\"Grybauskait\u0117\">{{cite news|title=The President attends the opening ceremony of Winter Olympics|url=https://www.lrp.lt/en/press-centre/press-releases/the-president-attends-the-opening-ceremony-of-winter-olympics/29355|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=President of the Republic of Lithuania|date=9 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Kosovo}} [[Kosovo]] - [[President of Kosovo|President]] [[Hashim Tha\u00e7i]]<ref name=\"rfekosovo\">{{cite news|author1=Alan Crosby|title=Winter Olympics Debut A 10th-Anniversary Gift For Kosovo|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/kosovo-winter-olympics-debut-10th-anniversary-independence-gift/29032362.html|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|date=10 February 2018|quote=Hashim Thaci, president of Kosovo, said on February 5 during a ceremony presenting the official Kosovar flag to Tahiri.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Luxembourg}} [[Luxembourg]] - [[Monarchy of Luxembourg|Grand Duke]] [[Henri, Grand Duke of Luxembourg|Henri]]<ref name=\"HenriPyeongChang\">{{cite news|title=Grand Duke Henri to Attend Winter Olympics|url=http://www.chronicle.lu/category/luxembourg/grand-duke-henri-to-attend-winter-olympics|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=Chronicle.lu}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Malaysia]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Najib Razak]]\n* {{flagicon|Monaco}} [[Monaco]] - [[Monarchy of Monaco|Prince]] [[Albert II, Prince of Monaco|Albert II]]<ref name=\"albertiiepa\">{{cite web|title=Prince Albert II of Monaco (C) reacts as he visits the House of Switzerland during the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Games, South Korea|url=http://www.epa.eu/sports-photos/alpine-skiing-photos/pyeongchang-2018-olympic-games-photos-54101554|website=european pressphoto agency|accessdate=10 February 2018}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Netherlands]] - [[Monarchy of the Netherlands|King]] [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands|Willem Alexander]], Queen [[Queen M\u00e1xima of the Netherlands|M\u00e1xima]] and [[Prime Minister of the Netherlands|Prime Minister]] [[Mark Rutte]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nos.nl/pyeongchang2018/artikel/2215477-koningspaar-en-premier-rutte-bij-openingsceremonie-pyeongchang.html|title=Koningspaar en premier Rutte bij openingsceremonie Pyeongchang|publisher=}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Norway]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Erna Solberg]]\n* {{flagicon|North Korea}} [[North Korea]] - [[President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly]] [[Kim Yong-nam]] and Vice Director of the [[Propaganda and Agitation Department]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] [[Kim Yo-jong]]<ref name=\"abcn_AtOl\">{{Cite web | title = At Olympic Games, Kim Jong Un's sister takes VIP seat | last = Talmadge | first = Eric | agency = AP | work = ABC News | date = 9 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-09 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/korea-delegation-led-kims-sister-arrives-olympics-52951272 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180209184355/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/korea-delegation-led-kims-sister-arrives-olympics-52951272 | archive-date = 9 February 2018 | url-status = dead | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Poland}} [[Poland]] - [[President of Poland|President]] [[Andrzej Duda]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/wiadomosci-z-kraju,3/wizyta-andrzeja-dudy-w-seulu-i-spotkanie-z-wiceprezydentem-usa,813345.html|title=Szczerski o rozmowie Dudy z wiceprezydentem USA: od razu wiadomo, \u017ce si\u0119 odb\u0119dzie|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Serbia}} [[Serbia]] - [[Ministry of Youth and Sports (Serbia)|Minister of Youth and Sports]] [[Vanja Udovi\u010di\u0107]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zurnal.rs/miks/zimski-sportovi/59723/zimske-olimpijske-igre-svecano-otvorene-u-pjoncangu|title=\u0417\u0438\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u043e\u043b\u0438\u043c\u043f\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0447\u0430\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435 \u0443 \u041f\u0458\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0443 \u2013 \u0421\u041f\u041e\u0420\u0422\u0421\u041a\u0418 \u0416\u0423\u0420\u041d\u0410\u041b|publisher=}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Slovakia}} [[Slovakia]] - [[President of Slovakia|President]] [[Andrej Kiska]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.news.naver.com/sports_general/news/read.nhn?oid=020&aid=0003119902&redirect=false|title=33\uac1c\uad6d \uc815\uc0c1\uae09 45\uba85 \ucc38\uc11d \ubc1d\ud600\u2026 \u9751 \uacbd\ud638\ucc98\uac00 \uadfc\uc811 \ubcf4\ud638|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Slovenia}} [[Slovenia]] - [[President of Slovenia|President]] [[Borut Pahor]]\n* {{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Sweden]] - [[King]] [[Carl XVI Gustaf]] and [[Queen regnant|Queen]] [[Silvia]]\n* {{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[Switzerland]] - [[President of the Swiss Confederation|President]] [[Alain Berset]]<ref name=\"Bersetlacote\">{{cite news|title=JO 2018: Alain Berset \u00e0 Pyeongchang pour affirmer la pr\u00e9sence de la Suisse|url=https://www.lacote.ch/dossiers/jeux-olympiques-d-hiver-de-pyeongchang-2018/articles/jo-2018-alain-berset-a-pyeongchang-pour-affirmer-la-presence-de-la-suisse-735478|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=La C\u00f4te|date=10 February 2018|language=french}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|UK}} [[Great Britain]] - [[Anne, Princess Royal]]<ref name=\"princessanne\">{{cite news|title=Guterres se reuni\u00f3 con el l\u00edder norcoreano Kim Yong-nam|url=http://www.dw.com/es/guterres-se-reuni%C3%B3-con-el-l%C3%ADder-norcoreano-kim-yong-nam/a-42526700|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Deutsche Welle]]|date=10 February 2018|language=spanish|quote=El secretario general de la ONU, Antonio Guterres, se encontr\u00f3 con el presidente nominal de Corea del Norte, Kim Yong-nam, en el marco de la inauguraci\u00f3n de los Juegos Ol\u00edmpicos de invierno en Pyeongchang.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} [[America]] - [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]] [[Mike Pence]] and [[Second Lady of the United States|Second Lady]] [[Karen Pence]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edaily.co.kr/news/news_detail.asp?newsId=03821206619076408&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|title=\u7f8e\ud39c\uc2a4, \uc62c\ub9bc\ud53d\ub300\ud45c\ub2e8 \ub04c\uace0 \ud3c9\ucc3d\u884c..\uc774\ubc29\uce74 \ucc38\uc11d\uc740 '\ubbf8\uc815'|date=10 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United Nations}} [[United Nations]] - [[Secretary-General of the United Nations|Secretary-General]] [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]]<ref name=\"guterresdw\">{{cite news|title=9 February 2018, Buckingham Palace|url=https://www.royal.uk/court-circular?text=&mrf=5&date%5Bmin%5D%5Bdate%5D=08%2F02%2F2018&date%5Bmax%5D%5Bdate%5D=09%2F02%2F2018&id=|accessdate=21 February 2018|agency=[[Court Circular]]|date=9 February 2018|language=english|quote=The Princess Royal, Member, International Olympic Committee, and President, British Olympic Association, this evening attended the Opening Reception and Ceremony of the XXIII Winter Olympic Games.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|IOC}} [[International Olympic Committee]] - [[President]] [[Thomas Bach]]\n\n[[File:Kim Yo-jong.jpg|thumb|upright|Kim Yo-jong attending the ceremony]]\nOn 9 February 2018, [[Kim Yo-jong]] \u2014 sister of [[Kim Jong-un]] \u2014 attended the ceremony in [[Pyeongchang]], South Korea. This was a first time that a member of the ruling [[Kim dynasty (North Korea)|Kim dynasty]] had visited South Korea since the [[Korean War]].<ref name=\"theg_USvi\">{{Cite web | title = US vice-president skips Olympics dinner in snub to North Korea officials | last = Haas | first = Benjamin | work = the Guardian | date = 9 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-09 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/feb/09/kim-jong-uns-sister-arrives-in-south-korea-for-winter-olympics }}</ref> Kim Yo-jong shook hands with South Korean president [[Moon Jae-in]] before sitting down to watch the ceremony together.<ref name=\"tele\" />\n\n==Anthems==\n*{{flagdeco|KOR}} [[Rainbow Children's Choir]] \u2013 [[Aegukga|South Korean National Anthem]]<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\"/>\n*{{flagdeco|IOC}} [[Sumi Hwang]] \u2013 [[Olympic Hymn]]<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\"/>\n\n==Ceremony key team==\n*Artistic Director: Yang Jung-woong<ref name=\"PerformatOpening\"/>\n*Executive Director, creative: Song Seung-whan<ref name=\"nanta\">{{cite news|title=Olympics-Pyeongchang picks 'Nanta' producer for 2018 ceremonies|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/olympics-pyeongchang-ceremonies/olympics-pyeongchang-picks-nanta-producer-for-2018-ceremonies-idUSL3N0ZI1P120150702|accessdate=1 February 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=2 July 2015|location=[[Seoul]], South Korea}}</ref>\n*Executive Director, cinematography: Lim Tae-hong, Andrew<ref name=\"nanta\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|2018 Winter Olympics opening ceremony}}\n* [https://library.olympic.org/Default/doc/SYRACUSE/172884/pyeongchang-2018-olympic-winter-games-opening-ceremony-media-guide-the-pyeongchang-organizing-commit?_lg=en-GB Pyeongchang 2018 Olympic Games Opening Ceremony Media Guide (as found on Olympic Library)] \n* [https://stillmed.olympic.org/media/Document%20Library/OlympicOrg/News/2018/02/opening-ceremony/President-speech-PyeongChang-2018-Opening-Ceremony.pdf#_ga=2.116249606.1670936625.1546721863-1292983301.1545348118 Thomas Bach, President of the International Olympic Committee's speech]\n*{{youtube|u7eiNnw6Kwc|PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony}}\n{{Olympic Games ceremonies}}\n{{Portal bar|Olympics|South Korea}}\n\n[[Category:2018 Winter Olympics|Opening Ceremony]]\n[[Category:Ceremonies in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Olympics opening ceremonies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox news event\n| title           = 2018 Winter Olympics<br />opening ceremony\n| image_name      = Opening ceremony DVo-tC7U0AAPyz3.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = [[Yuna Kim]], South Korean Olympic figure skating champion, lights the Olympic cauldron\n| date            = {{start date|df=yes|2018|02|09}}\n| time            = 20:00 \u2013 22:20 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]] ([[UTC+09:00|UTC+9]])\n| place           = [[Pyeongchang]], [[South Korea]]\n| coordinates     = {{coord|37|40|03|N|128|42|20|E|region:KR-42_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n| also known as   = Peace in Motion\n| filmed by       = [[Olympic Broadcasting Services|OBS]] on behalf of [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|footage={{youtube|u7eiNnw6Kwc|PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony}}\n| participants    = \n| awards          = \n| url             = \n}}\n{{2018 Winter Olympics}}\n\nThe '''[[Olympic opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2018 Winter Olympics]]''' was held at the [[Pyeongchang Olympic Stadium]] in [[Pyeongchang]], [[South Korea]] on 9 February 2018. It began at 20:00 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]] and finished at approximately 22:20 [[Korea Standard Time|KST]]. The Games were officially opened by [[President of the Republic of Korea]] [[Moon Jae-in]].\n\n==Preparations==\nThe site of the opening ceremony, [[Pyeongchang Olympic Stadium]], was built specifically for the Games. The pentagonal stadium seated 35,000. The organizers for the event said the shape was chosen because it is a combination of different shapes, a circle, a square, and a triangle, which represent heaven, earth, and mankind.<ref name=\"npr\" /><ref>https://abcnews.go.com/International/olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-peace-motion-kick-off/story?id=52930433</ref> No Olympic or Paralympic events were be held at the stadium, which was only used for the opening and closing ceremonies. The venue was torn down afterwards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.citylab.com/life/2018/02/its-time-for-the-pop-up-olympics/552896/|title=It's Time for the Pop-Up Olympics|last1=Eaton|first1=Joe|date=February 9, 2018|publisher=CITYLAB|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe broadcast of the Opening Ceremony of the 2018 Winter Olympic Games was available in more than 200 countries around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://2018winterolympicswiki.com/opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-2018-live-9-february-2018/917/|title=Pyeongchang 2018 Opening Ceremony LIVE on 9 February 2018|date=18 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref> \n*[[Ha Hyun-woo]] of the band [[Guckkasten]], [[Ahn Ji-young]] of the musical duo [[Bolbbalgan4]], [[Lee Eun-mi (singer)|Lee Eun-mi]] and [[Jeon In-kwon]] with his band Deulgukhwa performed and sang John Lennon's \"[[Imagine (John Lennon song)|Imagine]]\" at the opening ceremony.<ref name=\"PerformatOpening\">{{cite news|last1=Hong|first1=C.|title=Ha Hyun Woo, Bolbbalgan4\u2019s Ahn Ji Young, And More To Perform At Olympics Opening Ceremony|url=https://www.soompi.com/2018/01/30/ha-hyun-woo-bolbbalgan4s-ahn-ji-young-perform-2018-pyeongchang-olympics-opening-ceremony/|accessdate=1 February 2018|work=[[Soompi]]|publisher=[[Viki (website)|Viki, Inc.]]|date=30 January 2018}}</ref>\n*The Rainbow Children's Choir performed an arrangement, with Korean traditional musical instruments, of the national anthem, \u201c[[Aegukga]]\u201d.<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\">{{Cite web | title = Who Were the Singers at the Opening Ceremony of the Winter Olympics? | last = Garcia | first = Maira | work = nytimes.com | date = 10 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-11 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/10/arts/music/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-singers.html | quote =  }}</ref> The multiethnic children's choir was formed to educate the Korean public about multicultural families living in Korea.<ref>https://www.sbnation.com/2018/2/9/16979556/olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live-results-events-highlights</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/10/arts/music/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-singers.html|title=Who Were the Singers at the Opening Ceremony of the Winter Olympics?|last=Garcia|first=Maira|date=10 Feb 2018|website=PyeongChang 2018|access-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Insooni]] sang the theme song for the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Torch Relay, \"Let Everyone Shine\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BSyw06cGlJ8|title=(ENG) Theme song for the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Torch Relay (ENG sub)|first=|last=PyeongChang 2018|date=21 September 2017|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>https://www.olympicchannel.com/en/video/detail/opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-2018-replays/</ref>\n\n==Ceremony==\nThe ceremony's message centered on peace, passion, harmony, and convergence.<ref name=\"npr\">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetorch/2018/02/09/584368072/winter-olympics-opening-ceremony-pyeongchang-welcomes-the-world|title=Winter Olympics Opening Ceremony: Pyeongchang Welcomes The World|publisher=NPR|last1=Chappell|first1=Bill|date=February 9, 2018|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>https://www.businessinsider.com/2018-winter-olympics-the-best-photos-from-the-opening-ceremony-2018-2</ref>\n\nFive children from rural Gangwon province led the ceremony, which included one [[Inmyeonjo]] (a mythical creature with a body of a bird and a head of a human, a creature that only appears when the world is at peace), [[Four Symbols (China)|four mythical creatures]], including a white tiger \u2014 spirit animal protector of Korea and the mascot of these Games, natural floral and fauna, and a cast of 2,000. Five children were used to symbolize the five Olympic rings, and the five names were chosen to represent fire, water, wood, metal, and earth, the five elements that are believed to make up the Earth.<ref name=\"npr\" /><ref>https://www.olympic.org/news/pyeongchang-opening-ceremony-celebrates-culture</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/09/sports/olympics/opening-ceremony.html</ref>\n\n[[Augmented reality]] and [[5G]] technology were also incorporated in the event. The largest drone show in history, featuring 1,218 [[Shooting Star (drone)|Shooting Star drones]], was planned for the ceremony but cancelled at the last minute; television audiences were shown a version that had been recorded the previous December.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/olympics-opening-ceremony-drone-show/|title=Inside the Olympics Opening Ceremony World-Record Drone Show|work=WIRED|access-date=2018-02-09|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Banks|first1=Paul M.|title=Winter Olympics Verify Mike Pence Hypocrisy on NFL National Anthem Protests|url=http://www.chicagonow.com/patriotic-dissenter/2018/02/winter-olympics-verify-mike-pence-hypocrisy-on-nfl-national-anthem-protests/|accessdate=13 February 2018|work=[[ChicagoNow]]|date=9 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring the opening ceremony the organizing committee was a victim of a cyber attack, but without major consequences.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Meeks|first1=David|title=By not standing for Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics, VP Mike Pence embarrassed America|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/winter-olympics-2018/2018/02/12/vice-president-mike-pence-north-korea-embarrassed-america/328254002/|accessdate=13 February 2018|work=[[USA Today]]|date=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Programme==\n===Parade of Nations===\n{{main|2018 Winter Olympics Parade of Nations}}\nThe Parade of Nations was led, according to custom due to hosting the original [[ancient Olympics]], by the Greek team, followed by other competing countries in alphabetical order based on their names in the [[Korean language]], with the host country, South Korea, concluding the march.<ref name=\"Guardian\" />\n\nThe delegations from both the host nation [[South Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics|South Korea]] and [[North Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics|North Korea]] ([[Korea at the 2018 Winter Olympics]]) marched under the [[Korean unification flag]].<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/feb/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live |title=Winter Olympics 2018 opening ceremony \u2013 live!|date=9 February 2018|work=Guardian|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> South Korean [[Won Yun-jong]] and North Korean [[Hwang Chung-gum]] both held the flagpole.<ref name=\"tele\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2018/02/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-review-pyeongchang-unites/|title=Winter Olympics 2018 opening ceremony review: Pyeongchang unites the world in a blizzard of emotion and effects|publisher=The Telegraph|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Pence1\">{{cite news|last1=Radnofsky|first1=Louise|last2=Cheng|first2=Jonathan|title=Pence Sat During Opening Ceremony. Some Koreans Took Offense.|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/pence-sat-during-opening-ceremony-some-koreans-took-offense-1518259101|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nEven though the temperature in the stadium during the ceremony was very cold, Bermuda's delegation wore shorts and Tongan [[Pita Taufatofua]] repeated his shirtless and oiled up [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|Summer Olympic appearance]].<ref name=\"tele\" />\n\nBackground music for the parade began with an instrumental version of \"[[Hand in Hand (Olympic theme song)|Hand in Hand]]\" by [[Koreana (band)|Koreana]] and included modern dance remixes of songs such as \"\ub2e8\ubc1c\uba38\ub9ac\" by [[Cho Yong-pil]] and of traditional Korean music, as well as the following [[K-pop]] hits:  \"[[Gangnam Style]]\" by [[Psy]], \"[[Likey]]\" by [[Twice (band)|Twice]], \"[[Fantastic Baby]]\" by [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|Big Bang]], \"[[DNA (BTS song)|DNA]]\" by [[BTS (band)|BTS]], and \"[[Red Flavor]]\" by [[Red Velvet (band)|Red Velvet]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=6 December 2017|title=2018 Winter Olympics Kick Off With Korean Stars PSY & BTS During Opening Ceremonies|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8098906/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-psy-bts-skating-oasis-ed-sheeran|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> \"Red Flavor\" was cut off just as the unified Korean team was introduced.\n\n===Torch lighting===\n{{see also|2018 Winter Olympics torch relay}}\n[[File:PyeongChang 2018 Cauldron.jpg|thumb|right|Cauldron]]\n\nThe Olympic flame was on a 101-day relay across South Korea. The start of the ceremony takes place in Olympia of Greece. Apostles Angelis, 24 years old cross-country skier, is selected to be the first torchbearer. He said \"It is a great honour for me to be chosen as the first torchbearer for the Olympic Winter Games of 2018. It is truly a unique moment that I am looking forward to. I feel very proud and with a unique sense of happiness.\" <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/olympia-awaits-flame-lighting-ceremony-for-pyeongchang-2018|title=Olympia Awaits Flame Lighting Ceremony for PyeongChang 2018|last=|first=|date=19 October 2017|website=Olympic Games|access-date=}}</ref> Park Ji-Sung, football player in Republic of Korea, was the second person to hold the torch. After the flame touring around Greece for a week, it reached the Acropolis on 30th of October. <ref name=\":0\" /> There were 36 ceremonies held in different cities over a week, then the flame arrived to the PyeongChang Panathenaic Stadium. More than 500 torchbearers participated to follow the rituals of Olympic cycle, and carried the message of peace.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/information-to-the-media-pyeongchang-2018-olympic-flame-lighting-ceremony|title=Information to the Media - PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Flame-Lighting Ceremony|last=|first=|date=23 October 2017|website=Olympic Games|access-date=}}</ref> In the stadium, Opera soloist [[Sumi Hwang]] sang the [[Olympic anthem]] during the torch lighting ceremony. The final person to hold the torch was [[Inbee Park]], the golfer from Republic of Korea. [[Jong Su-hyon]] from North Korea and [[Park Jong-ah]] from South Korea carried the torch and headed up stairs toward the cauldron. <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/09/sports/olympics/opening-ceremony.html|title=Winter Olympics 2018 Opening Ceremony: Highlights and Analysis|last=Keh|first=Andrew|date=9 Feb 2018|website=PyeongChang 2018|access-date=}}</ref>As the torch neared the cauldron, an ice skating rink with South Korean figure skater [[Yuna Kim]] was revealed.<ref name=\"tele\" /> Yuna Kim is the well-known figure skater who won gold medal in 2010 and silver medal in 2014.<ref name=\":1\" /> The cauldron was designed to represent a full moon when it is not lit. Kim received the torch and lit the cauldron.<ref name=\"npr\" />\n\n===Wish Fire===\n\nThe final segment entitled \"Wish Fire\" featured Korean dance group Just Jerk<ref>[https://www.pyeongchang2018.com/en/news/behind-the-scenes-of-the-pyeongchang-2018-opening-ceremony Behind the Scenes of the PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony]</ref> (who became known internationally for their participation in the [[America's Got Talent (season 12)|twelfth season]] of ''[[America's Got Talent]]'') entered the stage dressed as [[Dokkaebi]], and performers with sparklers on roller blades. This segment in total featured 2,000 fireworks within and out of the stadium, some reaching as high as {{convert|1,300|m|ft}}.<ref name=\"npr\" />\n\n=== Intel\u00ae Drone Light Show ===\nMore than 1,200 Intel [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs)]] or drones flying above PyeongChang to celebrate the opening of 2018 Winter Olympic Games. Intel\u00ae drone team now holds the Guinness World Record of flying largest number of drones. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/sports/olympic-games/drones.html|title=Intel\u00ae Drones at The Olympic Games|last=|first=|date=|website=intel\u00ae|access-date=}}</ref> The drones flew together to form custom animations illustrating snow boarding, skiing, other different sports, as well as the [[Olympic symbols|iconic Olympic rings]]. The Shooting Star drones carried on the symbol of unity and progress from lighting of the torch. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/technology-innovation/aerial-technology-light-show.html|title=A Record-Breaking Show at PyeongChang 2018|last=|first=|date=2018|website=intel\u00ae|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===Russian hacking===\nOn 24 February, the ''[[Washington Post]]'' reported that U.S. intelligence uncovered [[Russia]]n spies hacked computers during the Opening Ceremony, an act that was previously speculated to be the work of North Korea. Analysts believed the Russians instigated the February 9 attack as a way to retaliate for the International Olympic Committee's decision to restrict the participation of Russian athletes in the 2018 Winter Olympics as punishment for doping violations.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/winter-olympics-2018/2018/02/25/winter-olympics-russian-spies-hacked-opening-ceremony-report/371051002/ Report: Russian spies behind Winter Olympics cyber attack]. ''US Today''. Retrieved 26 February 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.cnet.com/news/russian-spies-reportedly-hacked-winter-olympics-2018-washington-post/ Russian spies reportedly hacked Winter Olympics]. ''CNET''.  Retrieved 26 February 2018.</ref>\n\n==Dignitaries in attendance==\n[[File:Vice President Pence's Trip to Asia (28394490479).jpg|thumb|[[Mike Pence]], [[Vice President of the United States]]. With [[Moon Jae-in]], [[Thomas Bach]] and [[Kim Yo-jong]]]]\n\nAbout 25 heads of state attended the ceremony, in addition to the [[UN]] Secretary General. [[President of Russia]] [[Vladimir Putin]] was invited to attend, but declined due to the ban on Russian athletes by the [[IOC]].\n\n* {{flagicon|Finland}} [[Finland]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Juha Sipila]]\n* {{flagicon|France}} [[France]] - [[President (government title)|President]] [[Emmanuel Macron]], [[Ministry of Europe and Foreign Affairs|Minister of Europe and Foreign Affairs]] [[Jean-Yves Le Drian]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/politics/diplomacy/825180.html|title=\ud3c9\ucc3d \uc624\ub294 \uc678\uad6d\uc815\uc0c1 \ubc8c\uc368 15\uba85\u2026\u2018\uc62c\ub9bc\ud53d \uc678\uad50\u2019 \uaf43\ud53c\uc6b4\ub2e4|date=26 December 2017|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref> and [[Minister of Youth Affairs and Sports (France)|Minister of Sports]] [[Laura Flessel-Colovic|Laura Flessel]]\n* {{flagicon|Canada}} [[Canada]] - [[Governor General of Canada|Governor General]] [[Julie Payette]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/governor-general-payette-south-korea-olympics-1.4507777|title=Gov. Gen. Julie Payette to attend opening of winter Olympics|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"guard\" />\n* {{flagicon|China}} [[China]] - [[Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China|Politburo standing]] member [[Han Zheng]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bta.bg/en/gallery/image/4683766|title=SOUTH KOREA-CHINA-HAN ZHENG-WINTER OLYMPICS-OPENING CEREMONY|date=February 9, 2018|access-date=February 10, 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Colombia}} [[Colombia]] - [[Vice President of Colombia|Vice President]] [[\u00d3scar Naranjo]]<ref name=\"guard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2018/feb/09/winter-olympics-2018-opening-ceremony-live|title=Winter Olympics opening ceremony: Koreans enter under unified flag \u2013 as it happened|publisher=The Guardian|access-date=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Denmark]] - [[Crown Prince]] [[Frederick, Crown Prince of Denmark|Frederick]]\n* {{flagicon|Estonia}} [[Estonia]] - [[President of Estonia|President]] [[Kersti Kaljulaid]]<ref name=\"koreanetKaljulaid\">{{cite news|authorlink1=Kim Tae Won and Kim Young Shin|title=Korea-Estonia summit to help launch peace through Olympics|url=http://www.korea.net/NewsFocus/policies/view?articleId=153762|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=Korea.net|date=7 February 2018|quote=President Moon Jae-in held a meeting with President Kersti Kaljulaid of Estonia who is on a visit to Korea to attend the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Germany}} [[Germany]] - [[President of Germany|President]] [[Frank-Walter Steinmeier]]<ref name=\"dwspanishgermanypres\">{{cite news|title=Presidente de Alemania apoya di\u00e1logo entre Coreas|url=http://www.dw.com/es/presidente-de-alemania-apoya-di%C3%A1logo-entre-coreas/a-42531385|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=spanish}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Italy]] - Sports Minister of [[Italy]] Luca Lotti<ref name=\"lastampalotti\">{{cite news|author=Daniela Cotto|title=Il ministro Lotti a Casa Italia, l\u2019incontro con Lindsey Vonn|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2018/02/09/sport/speciali/olimpiadi-pyeongchang-2018/il-ministro-lotti-a-casa-italia-lincontro-con-lindsey-vonn-AqQhOx28jG9DmCvFllo2zL/pagina.html|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=La Stampa|date=9 February 2018|language=italian|archive-