}} [[Kosovo]] - [[President of Kosovo|President]] [[Hashim Tha\u00e7i]]<ref name=\"rfekosovo\">{{cite news|author1=Alan Crosby|title=Winter Olympics Debut A 10th-Anniversary Gift For Kosovo|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/kosovo-winter-olympics-debut-10th-anniversary-independence-gift/29032362.html|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|date=10 February 2018|quote=Hashim Thaci, president of Kosovo, said on February 5 during a ceremony presenting the official Kosovar flag to Tahiri.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Luxembourg}} [[Luxembourg]] - [[Monarchy of Luxembourg|Grand Duke]] [[Henri, Grand Duke of Luxembourg|Henri]]<ref name=\"HenriPyeongChang\">{{cite news|title=Grand Duke Henri to Attend Winter Olympics|url=http://www.chronicle.lu/category/luxembourg/grand-duke-henri-to-attend-winter-olympics|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=Chronicle.lu}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Malaysia]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Najib Razak]]\n* {{flagicon|Monaco}} [[Monaco]] - [[Monarchy of Monaco|Prince]] [[Albert II, Prince of Monaco|Albert II]]<ref name=\"albertiiepa\">{{cite web|title=Prince Albert II of Monaco (C) reacts as he visits the House of Switzerland during the PyeongChang 2018 Olympic Games, South Korea|url=http://www.epa.eu/sports-photos/alpine-skiing-photos/pyeongchang-2018-olympic-games-photos-54101554|website=european pressphoto agency|accessdate=10 February 2018}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Netherlands]] - [[Monarchy of the Netherlands|King]] [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands|Willem Alexander]], Queen [[Queen M\u00e1xima of the Netherlands|M\u00e1xima]] and [[Prime Minister of the Netherlands|Prime Minister]] [[Mark Rutte]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nos.nl/pyeongchang2018/artikel/2215477-koningspaar-en-premier-rutte-bij-openingsceremonie-pyeongchang.html|title=Koningspaar en premier Rutte bij openingsceremonie Pyeongchang|publisher=}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Norway]] - [[Prime Minister]] [[Erna Solberg]]\n* {{flagicon|North Korea}} [[North Korea]] - [[President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly]] [[Kim Yong-nam]] and Vice Director of the [[Propaganda and Agitation Department]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] [[Kim Yo-jong]]<ref name=\"abcn_AtOl\">{{Cite web | title = At Olympic Games, Kim Jong Un's sister takes VIP seat | last = Talmadge | first = Eric | agency = AP | work = ABC News | date = 9 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-09 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/korea-delegation-led-kims-sister-arrives-olympics-52951272 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180209184355/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/korea-delegation-led-kims-sister-arrives-olympics-52951272 | archive-date = 9 February 2018 | url-status = dead | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Poland}} [[Poland]] - [[President of Poland|President]] [[Andrzej Duda]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/wiadomosci-z-kraju,3/wizyta-andrzeja-dudy-w-seulu-i-spotkanie-z-wiceprezydentem-usa,813345.html|title=Szczerski o rozmowie Dudy z wiceprezydentem USA: od razu wiadomo, \u017ce si\u0119 odb\u0119dzie|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Serbia}} [[Serbia]] - [[Ministry of Youth and Sports (Serbia)|Minister of Youth and Sports]] [[Vanja Udovi\u010di\u0107]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zurnal.rs/miks/zimski-sportovi/59723/zimske-olimpijske-igre-svecano-otvorene-u-pjoncangu|title=\u0417\u0438\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u043e\u043b\u0438\u043c\u043f\u0438\u0458\u0441\u043a\u0435 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0447\u0430\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435 \u0443 \u041f\u0458\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0443 \u2013 \u0421\u041f\u041e\u0420\u0422\u0421\u041a\u0418 \u0416\u0423\u0420\u041d\u0410\u041b|publisher=}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Slovakia}} [[Slovakia]] - [[President of Slovakia|President]] [[Andrej Kiska]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.news.naver.com/sports_general/news/read.nhn?oid=020&aid=0003119902&redirect=false|title=33\uac1c\uad6d \uc815\uc0c1\uae09 45\uba85 \ucc38\uc11d \ubc1d\ud600\u2026 \u9751 \uacbd\ud638\ucc98\uac00 \uadfc\uc811 \ubcf4\ud638|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Slovenia}} [[Slovenia]] - [[President of Slovenia|President]] [[Borut Pahor]]\n* {{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Sweden]] - [[King]] [[Carl XVI Gustaf]] and [[Queen]] [[Silvia]]\n* {{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[Switzerland]] - [[President of the Swiss Confederation|President]] [[Alain Berset]]<ref name=\"Bersetlacote\">{{cite news|title=JO 2018: Alain Berset \u00e0 Pyeongchang pour affirmer la pr\u00e9sence de la Suisse|url=https://www.lacote.ch/dossiers/jeux-olympiques-d-hiver-de-pyeongchang-2018/articles/jo-2018-alain-berset-a-pyeongchang-pour-affirmer-la-presence-de-la-suisse-735478|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=La C\u00f4te|date=10 February 2018|language=french}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|UK}} [[Great Britain]] - [[Anne, Princess Royal]]<ref name=\"princessanne\">{{cite news|title=Guterres se reuni\u00f3 con el l\u00edder norcoreano Kim Yong-nam|url=http://www.dw.com/es/guterres-se-reuni%C3%B3-con-el-l%C3%ADder-norcoreano-kim-yong-nam/a-42526700|accessdate=10 February 2018|agency=[[Deutsche Welle]]|date=10 February 2018|language=spanish|quote=El secretario general de la ONU, Antonio Guterres, se encontr\u00f3 con el presidente nominal de Corea del Norte, Kim Yong-nam, en el marco de la inauguraci\u00f3n de los Juegos Ol\u00edmpicos de invierno en Pyeongchang.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United States}} [[America]] - [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]] [[Mike Pence]] and [[Second Lady of the United States|Second Lady]] [[Karen Pence]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edaily.co.kr/news/news_detail.asp?newsId=03821206619076408&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|title=\u7f8e\ud39c\uc2a4, \uc62c\ub9bc\ud53d\ub300\ud45c\ub2e8 \ub04c\uace0 \ud3c9\ucc3d\u884c..\uc774\ubc29\uce74 \ucc38\uc11d\uc740 '\ubbf8\uc815'|date=10 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=8 February 2018}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|United Nations}} [[United Nations]] - [[Secretary-General of the United Nations|Secretary-General]] [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]]<ref name=\"guterresdw\">{{cite news|title=9 February 2018, Buckingham Palace|url=https://www.royal.uk/court-circular?text=&mrf=5&date%5Bmin%5D%5Bdate%5D=08%2F02%2F2018&date%5Bmax%5D%5Bdate%5D=09%2F02%2F2018&id=|accessdate=21 February 2018|agency=[[Court Circular]]|date=9 February 2018|language=english|quote=The Princess Royal, Member, International Olympic Committee, and President, British Olympic Association, this evening attended the Opening Reception and Ceremony of the XXIII Winter Olympic Games.}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|IOC}} [[International Olympic Committee]] - [[President]] [[Thomas Bach]]\n\n[[File:Kim Yo-jong.jpg|thumb|upright|Kim Yo-jong attending the ceremony]]\nOn 9 February 2018, [[Kim Yo-jong]] \u2014 sister of [[Kim Jong-un]] \u2014 attended the ceremony in [[Pyeongchang]], South Korea. This was a first time that a member of the ruling [[Kim dynasty (North Korea)|Kim dynasty]] had visited South Korea since the [[Korean War]].<ref name=\"theg_USvi\">{{Cite web | title = US vice-president skips Olympics dinner in snub to North Korea officials | last = Haas | first = Benjamin | work = the Guardian | date = 9 February 2018 | accessdate = 2018-02-09 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/feb/09/kim-jong-uns-sister-arrives-in-south-korea-for-winter-olympics }}</ref> Kim Yo-jong shook hands with South Korean president [[Moon Jae-in]] before sitting down to watch the ceremony together.<ref name=\"tele\" />\n\n==Anthems==\n*{{flagdeco|KOR}} [[Rainbow Children's Choir]] \u2013 [[Aegukga|South Korean National Anthem]]<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\"/>\n*{{flagdeco|IOC}} [[Sumi Hwang]] \u2013 [[Olympic Hymn]]<ref name=\"nyti_WhoW\"/>\n\n==Ceremony key team==\n*Artistic Director: Yang Jung-woong<ref name=\"PerformatOpening\"/>\n*Executive Director, creative: Song Seung-whan<ref name=\"nanta\">{{cite news|title=Olympics-Pyeongchang picks 'Nanta' producer for 2018 ceremonies|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/olympics-pyeongchang-ceremonies/olympics-pyeongchang-picks-nanta-producer-for-2018-ceremonies-idUSL3N0ZI1P120150702|accessdate=1 February 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=2 July 2015|location=[[Seoul]], South Korea}}</ref>\n*Executive Director, cinematography: Lim Tae-hong, Andrew<ref name=\"nanta\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|2018 Winter Olympics opening ceremony}}\n* [https://library.olympic.org/Default/doc/SYRACUSE/172884/pyeongchang-2018-olympic-winter-games-opening-ceremony-media-guide-the-pyeongchang-organizing-commit?_lg=en-GB Pyeongchang 2018 Olympic Games Opening Ceremony Media Guide (as found on Olympic Library)] \n* [https://stillmed.olympic.org/media/Document%20Library/OlympicOrg/News/2018/02/opening-ceremony/President-speech-PyeongChang-2018-Opening-Ceremony.pdf#_ga=2.116249606.1670936625.1546721863-1292983301.1545348118 Thomas Bach, President of the International Olympic Committee's speech]\n*{{youtube|u7eiNnw6Kwc|PyeongChang 2018 Opening Ceremony}}\n{{Olympic Games ceremonies}}\n{{Portal bar|Olympics|South Korea}}\n\n[[Category:2018 Winter Olympics|Opening Ceremony]]\n[[Category:Ceremonies in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Olympics opening ceremonies]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toQueen(link changed toQueen regnant) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Winter_Olympics_opening_ceremony"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Singapore}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore\n| map2            = COVID-19 Cases in Singapore by Planning Areas.svg\n| legend2         = {{center|Map of planning areas with confirmed (red) coronavirus cases (as of 9 April)}}\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Singapore]]\n| first_case      = \n| arrival_date    = 23 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| recovery_cases  = 528<ref name=\"worldometers\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ |title=worldometers.info |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129195657/https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ |archive-date=29 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| deaths          = 8<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\">{{Cite web |url=https://coronaboard.com/ |title=COVID-19 Dashboard |access-date=5 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331135805/https://coronaboard.com/ |archive-date=31 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 2,299<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.coronatracker.com/country/sg |title=Corona Tracker Overview |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325143811/https://www.coronatracker.com/country/sg/ |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| Action taken: Circuit Braker (7 Apr-4 May 2020)\nStatus: Enforcing (Expires: 4 May 2020; Tentative)\n| active          = \n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{url|https://www.moh.gov.sg/covid-19}}\n| First Case detected: = \n}}\nThe '''2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore''' is part of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing global pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2). The first case of COVID-19 was confirmed on 23 January.<ref name=\"Abdullah 2020\" /> To combat COVID-19, a multi-ministerial committee was formed on 22 January with Minister for National Development [[Lawrence Wong]] and Minister for Health [[Gan Kim Yong]] as the co-chairs and [[Prime Minister of Singapore|Prime Minister]] [[Lee Hsien Loong]] and [[Deputy Prime Minister of Singapore|Deputy Prime Minister]] and Minister for Finance [[Heng Swee Keat]] as advisors.<ref name=\"ST22Jan\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/default-document-library/multi-ministry-taskforce-on-wuhan-coronavirus-and-tor---final.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321054236/https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/default-document-library/multi-ministry-taskforce-on-wuhan-coronavirus-and-tor---final.pdf |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April, Singapore announced a stringent set of preventive measures which were collectively called a 'circuit breaker'. This will be applied from 7 April to 4 May 2020.\n[[Singapore]] contributed US$500,000 to support [[WHO]] efforts against COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |title=Singapore contributes US$500,000 to support WHO efforts against COVID-19 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-contributes-s-500-000-to-support-who-covid-19-efforts-12568566 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=CNA |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325020159/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-contributes-s-500-000-to-support-who-covid-19-efforts-12568566 |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Singapore medical cases chart}}\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Statistics ==\nThe top plot shows the total number of cases as a function of time (by date) since 23 January 2020, the date of the first reported case in Singapore. The bottom plot shows the number of new cases as reported each day.\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|colors=orange, blue, red\n| legend=Legend\n| width = 900\n| height = 350\n| xAxisTitle = Date (day/month)\n| yAxisTitle = Total no. of cases (cumulative)\n| y1Title=Confirmed\n| y2Title=Recovered\n| y3Title=Deaths\n| xAxisAngle = -65\n| yGrid= |xGrid= \n| x =  23/1, 24/1, 25/1, 26/1, 27/1, 28/1, 29/1, 30/1, 31/1, 1/2, 2/2, 3/2, 4/2, 5/2, 6/2, 7/2, 8/2, 9/2, 10/2, 11/2, 12/2, 13/2, 14/2, 15/2, 16/2, 17/2, 18/2, 19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23/2, 24/2, 25/2, 26/2, 27/2, 28/2, 29/2, 1/3, 2/3, 3/3, 4/3, 5/3, 6/3, 7/3, 8/3, 9/3, 10/3, 11/3, 12/3, 13/3, 14/3, 15/3, 16/3, 17/3, 18/3, 19/3, 20/3, 21/3, 22/3, 23/3, 24/3, 25/3, 26/3, 27/3, 28/3, 29/3, 30/3, 31/3, 1/4, 2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 5/4, 6/4, 7/4, 8/4, 9/4, 10/4, 11/4\n| y1 = 1, 3, 3, 4, 5, 7, 10, 13, 16, 18, 18, 18, 24, 28, 30, 33, 40, 43, 45, 47, 50, 58, 67, 72, 75