title=The Tashkent Files review: A tacky thriller that feels longer than the Cold War|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-04-26}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/the-tashkent-files-review-film-by-vivek-agnihotri-doesnt-solve-mystery-shashtri-death|title='The Tashkent Files' \u2013 Prejudiced, Amateurish and Cringe-Worthy|date=2019-04-12|website=The Quint|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>Agnihotri was honoured by the [[Indian Film & Television Directors\u2019 Association]] for the box-office success of the movie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.co.in/vivek-ranjan-agnihotri-honoured-indian-film-television-directors%E2%80%99-association|title=Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri honoured by Indian Film & Television Directors' Association|date=2019-07-10|website=Box Office India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\nAs of {{As of|2020|alt=early 2020}}, Agnihotri is working on ''The Kashmir Files'', a film chronicling the \"unreported history of Kashmiri Hindus\" which is scheduled to be released on 15 August 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-bollywood-turns-to-plight-of-kashmiri-pandits-at-last/346096|title=Bollywood Turns To Plight Of Kashmiri Pandits, At Last|last=|first=|date=|website=Outlook India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/vivek-agnihotri-film-the-kashmir-files-to-release-in-august-2020-not-an-easy-story-to-tell-1580680-2019-08-14|title=Vivek Agnihotri film The Kashmir Files to release in August 2020: Not an easy story to tell|last=MumbaiAugust 14|first=Indo Asian News Service|last2=August 14|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31|last3=Ist|first3=2019 12:47}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/entertainment/after-the-tashkent-files-vivek-agnihotris-next-titled-the-kashmir-files-starring-anupam-kher|title=After 'The Tashkent Files', Vivek Agnihotri's next titled 'The Kashmir Files' starring Anupam Kher|website=Free Press Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref>\n\n==== Short films ====\nAgnihotri's short film ''Mohammad and Urvashi'' won a [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] for best actor in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|last=IANS|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vivek-agnihotri-s-mohammad-and-urvashi-bags-dadasaheb-phalke-award-movie-snippets-117051300491_1.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's 'Mohammad and Urvashi' bags Dadasaheb Phalke award (Movie Snippets)|date=2017-05-13|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> His film was released the following year and he said he received threats for using the name Mohammad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=IANS|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vivek-agnihotri-s-mohammad-and-urvashi-to-release-on-april-24-118041400542_1.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's 'Mohammad and Urvashi' to release on April 24|date=2018-04-14|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/vivek-agnihotri-claims-getting-threats-mohammad-urvashi-1502625275.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri claims getting threats over 'Mohammad And Urvashi'|date=2018-04-20|website=The Statesman|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Film certification ===\nIn 2017, Agnihotri was selected as convenor by the [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting (India)|Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]] in the preview committee of [[48th International Film Festival of India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/film/40-member-panel-films-iffi-agnihotri|title=Forty-Member Panel to Curate Films for IFFI With Agnihotri As Convenor|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> The same year, he was selected as member on board of India's [[Central Board of Film Certification]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/entertainment/pahlaj-nihalani-replaced-by-prasoon-joshi-vidya-balan-vivek-agnihotri-in-cbfc-board-meet-all-new-members/804733/|title=Pahlaj Nihalani replaced by Prasoon Joshi: Vidya Balan, Vivek Agnihotri in CBFC Board; meet all new members|date=2017-08-11|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/latest/846952/pahlaj-nihalani-removed-as-chief-of-central-board-of-film-certification|title=Pahlaj Nihalani removed as chief of Central Board of Film Certification|last=Staff|first=Scroll|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n=== Political activism ===\nAgnihotri has been frequently associated with the [[Right-wing politics|right wing]] and pro-[[BJP]] people by media but he rejects these descriptions and self-identifies as \"India-Wing\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/Neither-left-nor-right/article14244082.ece|title=Neither left, nor right|last=Dundoo|first=Sangeetha Devi|date=2016-04-18|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-11-06|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/releasing-the-tashkent-files-now-public-current-mood-vivek-agnihotri-5642358/|title=Releasing The Tashkent Files now due to public's current mood: Vivek Agnihotri|date=2019-03-25|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/vivekagnihotri/status/906510118136762371?lang=en|title=I have no wing. The only wing I know is 'India wing'. The day left-liberals start talking in favour of India & Indians, I'll support them.|last=Agnihotri|first=Vivek Ranjan|date=2017-09-09|website=@vivekagnihotri|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|last=Agrawal|first=Soniya|date=2018-08-29|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n[[File:Vivek Agnihotri.jpg|thumb|Vivek Agnihotri with his book ''Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam'']]\n\n====''Urban Naxals''====\nIn 2018, Vivek wrote [[Buddha in a Traffic Jam# Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam|''Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam'']],<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/not-easy-to-attract-eyeballs-from-government-vivek-agnihotri-118061500802_1.html |title=Not easy to attract eyeballs from government: Vivek Agnihotri |author=IANS |date=15 June 2018 |work=Business Standard India |access-date=20 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/lifestyle/books/2018/jul/08/vivek-agnihotris-urban-naxals-the-making-of-buddha-in-a-traffic-jam--going-beyond-the-maoist-myth-1838808.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam {{!}} Going beyond the Maoist myth|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indictoday.com/reviews/review-urban-naxals-the-making-of-buddha-in-a-traffic-jam-by-vivek-agnihotri/|title=Urban Naxals - The Making of Buddha In A Traffic Jam|date=2018-05-30|website=Indic Today|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> in which he described individuals in academia and media who were allegedly colluding with [[Naxalite]]s in a bid to overthrow the Indian government and were thus \"invisible enemies of India\" as \"Urban Naxals\".<ref name=\"ThePrint 2018\">{{cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|date=29 August 2018|website=ThePrint|access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> \n\nCritics said the term is \"vague rhetoric\" that is designed to discredit intellectuals who are critical of the establishment and political right and to stifle dissent.<ref name=UNaxals>Coverage and commentary on the term in mainstream media:\n*{{cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|date=29 August 2018|website=ThePrint|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/swara-bhasker-urban-naxals-1329970-2018-09-02|title=Swara Bhasker on Urban Naxals: You cannot punish people for thinking|language=en|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsclick.in/anti-national-urban-naxal-trajectory-dissent-india|title=From Anti-National to Urban Naxal: The Trajectory of Dissent in India|date=18 September 2018|website=NewsClick|language=en|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/conversations-with-urban-naxals-2-meghnad-everybody-who-does-not-agree-with-vivek-agnihotri-is-an-urban-naxal-5106411.html|title=Conversations with|website=Firstpost|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-45294286|title=Why India activist arrests sparked outrage|date=31 August 2018|access-date=26 March 2019|language=en-GB}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.arre.co.in/social-commentary/urban-naxal-uapa-arrests-bhima-koregaon/|title=What Makes An Urban Naxal?|date=29 August 2018|website=Arr\u00e9|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/news/column/a-propaganda-tool-called-urbannaxal/20180713.htm|title=A propaganda tool called #UrbanNaxal|website=Rediff|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Vivashwan|date=5 June 2015|title='Ghoul' and the Spectre of Totalitarianism|url=https://www.epw.in/engage/article/%E2%80%98ghoul%E2%80%99-and-spectre-totalitarianism|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|language=en|volume=53|issue=42}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-weekend/just-another-day-in-paradise/article24898900.ece|title=Just another day in paradise|last=Roy|first=Vaishna|date=2018-09-08|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=UNaxalsScholarly>Coverage and commentary on the term in scholarly sources:\n*{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Mohinder|last2=Dasgupta|first2=Rajarshi|date=2 January 2019|title=Exceptionalising democratic dissent: a study of the JNU event and its representations|journal=Postcolonial Studies|volume=22|issue=1|pages=59\u201378|doi=10.1080/13688790.2019.1568169|issn=1368-8790}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Udupa|first=Sahana|date=July 2019|title=Nationalism in the Digital Age : Fun as a Metapractice of Extreme Speech|url=https://ijoc.org/index.php/ijoc/article/view/9105/2715|journal=International Journal of Communication|volume=13|pages=3148|issn=1932-8036}}</ref> Reviews in the [[Organiser (magazine)|Organiser]] and [[The New Indian Express]] had praised the work.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.organiser.org//Encyc/2018/5/28/Urban-Naxals.html|title=Book Review: The Untold Story of Communist Terrorism|website=www.organiser.org|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|Union Minister of Human Resource Development]] [[Smriti Irani]] endorsed Vivek's views of [[Jadavpur University]] and [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] being breeding grounds of \"anti-national elements\" for having refused to screen ''Buddha in a Traffic Jam.''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Vivashwan|date=5 June 2015|title='Ghoul' and the Spectre of Totalitarianism|url=https://www.epw.in/engage/article/%E2%80%98ghoul%E2%80%99-and-spectre-totalitarianism|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|language=en|volume=53|issue=42|pages=7\u20138|via=}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nVivek is married to the Indian actor [[Pallavi Joshi]] and has two children.<ref name=\"ThePrint 2018\" /><ref name=\":3\" />\n\n=== Allegation of sexual harassment ===\nBollywood actor [[Tanushree Dutta]] had accused Vivek of inappropriate behaviour during the filming of [[Chocolate (2005 film)|Chocolate]]. He allegedly asked her to strip and dance to give expression cues to her male co-star [[Irrfan Khan]] during a close-up shot and retreated only after Irrfan and [[Suniel Shetty]] rebuffed him. Vivek had refuted the allegations as \"false and frivolous\", and filed a defamation case against Dutta.<ref name=\"Dutta\">Sources covering the episode:\n\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/tanushree-dutta-alleges-vivek-agnihotri-had-told-her-kapde-utaar-ke-naacho-1351645-2018-09-28|title=Tanushree Dutta alleges Vivek Agnihotri had told her 'kapde utaar ke naacho'|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/tanushree-dutta-accuses-vivek-agnihotri-of-harassment-says-irrfan-suniel-shetty-stood-up-for-her/story-5rFd0z3wycqhIq4LgCuTmI.html|title=Tanushree Dutta accuses Vivek Agnihotri of harassment, says Irrfan, Suniel Shetty stood up for her|date=28 September 2018|website=www.hindustantimes.com|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vivek-agnihotri-refutes-tanushree-dutta-allegations-5385901/|title=Vivek Agnihotri refutes Tanushree Dutta's allegations: Lawyer|date=4 October 2018|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vivek-agnihotri-calls-tanushree-duttas-allegations-false-frivolous/articleshow/66080260.cms|title=Vivek Agnihotri calls Tanushree Dutta's allegations \"false, frivolous\"|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Starkey|first=Jesse C.|last2=Koerber|first2=Amy|last3=Sternadori|first3=Miglena|last4=Pitchford|first4=Bethany|date=1 October 2019|title=#MeToo Goes Global: Media Framing of Silence Breakers in Four National Settings|journal=Journal of Communication Inquiry|language=en|volume=43|issue=4|pages=437\u2013461|doi=10.1177/0196859919865254|issn=0196-8599}}</ref> Sattyajit Gazmer, the film's assistant director, has also refuted Tanushree's allegations.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/assistant-director-turns-down-tanushree-dutta-s-claims-gives-detailed-account-of-the-incident-on-sets-of-chocolate/story-OXwgzv0eeFCwDyCLKc79LL.html|title=Assistant director turns down Tanushree Dutta's claims, gives detailed account of the incident on sets of Chocolate|date=2018-10-05|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/tanushree-dutta-controversy-chocolates-associate-director-ranjit-shah-comes-support-vivek-agnihotri-slams-actress-calls-erratic/|title=Tanushree Dutta controversy: Chocolate's associate director Ranjit Shah comes in support of Vivek Agnihotri, SLAMS the actress and calls her erratic : Bollywood News - Bollywood Hungama|last=Hungama|first=Bollywood|date=2018-10-06|language=en|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/entertainment/not-strip-but-take-off-bathrobe-worn-above-costume-chocolate-associate-director-sattyajit-gazmer-on-tanushree-duttas-allegations|title=Not strip, but take off bathrobe worn above costume: 'Chocolate' Associate Director Sattyajit Gazmer on Tanushree Dutta's allegations|website=Free Press Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Twitter ===\nFact checkers have noted Agnihotri to have shared [[Fake news in India|misleading content]] from his [[Twitter]] account.<ref name= fake> Sources which say Agnihotri shared misleading content\n*{{Cite web|url= https://theprint.in/hoaxposed/2018s-top-10-fake-news-from-pak-zindabad-to-post-claiming-congress-most-corrupt-party/167317/ |title=2018's top 10 fake news: From 'Pak zindabad' to post claiming Congress most 'corrupt party' |last=Rampal |first=Nikhil |date=25 December 2018|website=The Print |access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/vivek-agnihotri-makes-false-claim-of-nehru-responsible-for-outcome-of-1965-indo-pak-war/|title=Vivek Agnihotri makes false claim of Nehru responsible for outcome of 1965 Indo-Pak war|last=Sidharth|first=Arjun|date=11 March 2019|website=Alt News|language=en-GB|access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.boomlive.in/vivek-agnihotri-tweets-misleading-video-of-kanhaiya-kumar-speaking-about-islam/|title=Vivek Agnihotri Tweets Misleading Video Of Kanhaiya Kumar Speaking About Islam {{!}} BOOM|last=Team|first=BOOM FACT Check|date=12 November 2018|website=boomlive.in|access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/cannabis-kills-coronavirus-vivek-agnihotri-shares-scientific-misinformation-via-meme/|title=Cannabis kills coronavirus? Vivek Agnihotri shares scientific misinformation via meme|last=Chaudhuri|first=Pooja|date=2020-02-08|website=Alt News|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boomlive.in/fake-news/vivek-agnihotri-posts-a-doctored-image-of-anti-caa-protester-6530|title=Vivek Agnihotri Posts A Doctored Image Of Anti-CAA Protester|last=Chowdhury|first=Archis|date=2020-01-10|website=www.boomlive.in|language=en|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> In September 2018, Twitter had locked his account until he agreed to delete a tweet abusing [[Swara Bhaskar]]. In response to Swara calling out politician [[P. C. George]], who called an alleged rape victim a prostitute, Vivek tweeted \"Where is the placard - '#MeTooProstituteNun'?\". The tweet was interpreted as calling Swara a prostitute. Agnihotri defended his tweet and said he was making a point about the placarding by liberals at selective instances of alleged perpetrators belonging to the Hindu community.<ref name=\"Swara\">Sources covering the episode:\n\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-vivek-agnihotri-calls-swara-bhasker-a-prostitute-she-single-handedly-gets-his-twitter-account-locked-2661761|title=Vivek Agnihotri calls Swara Bhasker a 'prostitute', she single-handedly gets his Twitter account locked|date=11 September 2018|website=DNA India|language=en|access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vivek-agnihotri-forced-to-delete-abusive-tweet-against-swara-bhasker/articleshow/65762164.cms|title=Vivek Agnihotri forced to delete abusive tweet against Swara Bhasker|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatimes.com/entertainment/after-deletion-of-his-tweet-vivek-agnihotri-thanks-swara-bhasker-for-curbing-his-freedom-of-expression-352880.html|title=After Deletion Of His Tweet, Vivek 'Thanks' Swara Bhasker For Curbing His Freedom Of Expression|date=12 September 2018|website=indiatimes.com|language=en|access-date=12 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/120918/standing-up-against-abuse.html|title=Standing up against abuse|last=Srivastava|first=Namrata|date=12 September 2018|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en|access-date=15 March 2019}}</ref> In January 2018,  Agnihotri was accused of engaging in \"casteist commentary\" on Twitter after he said the flying of a [[Dalit]] leader's grandson in business class, when Agnihotri was flying in economy class despite being a [[Brahmin]], was [[reverse discrimination]].<ref name=\"Casteism\">Sources covering the episode:\n\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/agnihotri-dalit-tweet-brahmin-flight-economy-class-business-class-neeraj-ghaywan-cannes-twitter-sparks-outrage-twitter.html|title=Agnihotri's 'dalit-brahmin' tweet sparks Twitter outrage|website=theweek.in|access-date=27 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/neeraj-ghaywan-responds-to-vivek-agnihotris-dalit-tweet-twitter-lines-up-in-support-of-the-masaan-director-4286357.html|title=Neeraj Ghaywan responds to Vivek Agnihotri's Dalit tweet; Twitter lines up in support of the Masaan director- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=4 January 2018|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=27 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/neeraj-ghaywan-responds-to-vivek-agnihotris-casteist-tweet-says-won-cannes-award-without-using-his-dalit-identity-1622757.html|title=Neeraj Ghaywan Responds To Vivek Agnihotri's Casteist Tweet, Says Won Cannes Award Without Using His Dalit Identity|website=News18|access-date=27 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/neon/social-buzz/neeraj-ghaywan-on-dalit-trolls|title='Masaan' Director Neeraj Ghaywan Shuts Down Casteist Trolls, & How|date=3 January 2018|website=The Quint|language=en|access-date=27 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/050118/neeraj-ghaywan-shut-vivek-agnihotri-like-a-boss-but-twitteratis-cant-stop-fighting.html|title=Neeraj Ghaywan shut Vivek Agnihotri like a boss, but Twitteratis can't stop fighting|date=5 January 2018|website=Deccan Chronicle|language=en|access-date=27 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/caste/neeraj-ghaywan-interview-job-call-diversity-bollywood|title=Interview: Director Neeraj Ghaywan on Why His Job Call Seeks Bahujan Talent|website=The Wire|access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes and references==\n===Notes===\n{{Notelist}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External Links==\n{{IMDb name|nm1892252}}\n\n{{Vivek Agnihotri}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Agnihotri, Vivek}}\n[[Category:Hindi-language film directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian film directors]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Kendriya Vidyalaya alumni]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:People from Gwalior]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian director, screenwriter and author}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vivek Agnihotri\n| image              = Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri (cropped).jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| occupation         = Director, screenwriter, author\n| birth_place        = [[Gwalior]], India\n| spouse             = [[Pallavi Joshi]]\n| children           = 2\n| birth_date         = \n| education          = [[Indian Institute of Mass Communication]]\n| years_active       = \n| parents            = \n| website            = {{url|https://vivekagnihotri.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri''' is an Indian film director, screenwriter, and author. As of 2019, he is member of the board of India's [[Central Board of Film Certification]]. \n\nAgnihotri started his career with advertorial agencies and moved to producing and directing tele-serials; his work has been positively received. He debuted in Bollywood with the crime thriller [[Chocolate (2005 film)|''Chocolate'']] (2005) and went on to direct multiple films. With the exception of [[The Tashkent Files]] and [[Hate Story]], his films have received mostly poor reviews from critics and have under-performed at box-office. In 2017, his first short film ''Mohammad and Urvashi'' won the [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] for best actor.\n\nAgnihotri has been frequently associated with the [[Right-wing politics|right wing]] (and [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]) by media and has been subject to controversies; he though rejects the tag and self-identifies as ''India-Wing.''\n\n== Early life and education ==\nVivek Agnihotri was born in [[Gwalior]], [[Madhya Pradesh]] to Prabhudayal Agnihotri and Ranjan Agnihotri.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nHe studied at the [[Indian Institute of Mass Communication]] before enrolling at [[Harvard Extension School]] for a Certificate of Special Studies in Administration and Management.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiantelevision.com/interviews/director/vivek1.htm|title=\"Terrorism interests and fascinates me\":Vivek Agnihotri|date=2002-01-02|website=Indian Television Dot Com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://vivekagnihotri.com/who-is-vivek-agnihotri/|title=About|website=Vivek Agnihotri|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>{{Efn|CSS was started in 1980 as a certificate course for students with a bachelor's degree but no prior training in business or management.<ref name=\"CSS\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/The_Gates_Unbarred.html?id=qOsSCUXn1SUC|title=\"The Gates Unbarred\": A History of University Extension at Harvard, 1910-2009|last=Shinagel|first=Michael|date=2009|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-03616-1|language=en}}</ref>{{Rp|130}} In 2007 it was converted into a full Master of Liberal Arts in Extension Studies (ALM) in management.<ref name=\"CSS\" />{{Rp|200}}}} In interviews with media, he has also mentioned [[Bhopal School of Social Sciences]] and [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] among his ''[[Alma mater|almae matres]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tNkqp9vcVcY&t=2s|title=Risk it with Ravijot - Talk 01, Vivek Agnihotri|last=Nationalist Ravi|date=16 June 2016 |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/entertainment/vivek-agnihotri-on-the-contrarian-kanhaiya-kumar/article8450118.ece|title=The contrarian Kanhaiya Kumar|last=Modi|first=Chintan Girish|date=2016-04-08|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-10-29|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Advertising and television serials ===\nAgnihotri started his career with the advertising agencies [[Ogilvy (agency)|Ogilvy]] and [[McCann (company)|McCann]], and served as creative director for campaigns of Gillette and Coca Cola.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" /> In 1994, he became involved with the directing and production of several television serials; his work was positively received.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiantelevision.com/interviews/director/vivek.htm|title='How soon the viewer flows into the story determines my success' : Vivek Agnihotri|date=2001-06-06|website=Indian Television Dot Com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/the-chocolate-lawyer/article28183638.ece|title=The chocolate lawyer|date=2005-09-19|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/one-gearing-up-to-two/article28213842.ece|title=One... gearing up to two!|date=2005-11-14|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n=== Filmography ===\n\n==== Feature films ====\nVivek debuted in [[Bollywood]] with ''[[Chocolate (2005 film)|Chocolate]]'' (2005), which is a remake of the 1995 Hollywood neo-noir crime thriller ''[[The Usual Suspects]]''. Critical reception of the movie was negative<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/films/2005/09/16/chocolate_2005_review.shtml |title=Jaspreet Pandohar review of Chocolate (Deep Dark Secrets) (2005)|date=2005-09-11 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=4 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/shoplifted-and-shopworn/article28586523.ece|title=Shoplifted and shopworn|date=2005-09-23|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> and included accusations of [[plagiarism]]{{fact|date=April 2020}}, and the film fared poorly at box office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=420|title=Chocolate - Movie - Box Office India|website=boxofficeindia.com|access-date=23 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/Business-meets-Bollywood/article15461380.ece|title=Business meets Bollywood|last=Dundoo|first=Sangeetha Devi|date=2011-02-28|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> ''[[Goal (2007 Hindi film)|Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal]]'' is about an all-Asian football team in the United Kingdom that wins trophies while fighting on-field discrimination and the local municipality that wants to sell the team's ground.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=FLNZDwAAQBAJ|title=The British Football Film|last=Glynn|first=Stephen|date=3 May 2018|publisher=Springer|isbn=9783319777276 |pages=137|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=mFjSCwAAQBAJ|title=Bollywood in Britain: Cinema, Brand, Discursive Complex|last=Kr\u00e4mer|first=Lucia|date=2 June 2016|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing USA|isbn=9781501307584 |pages=74\u201378|language=en}}</ref> It received poor reception from critics<ref name=\"DDDG\">Reviews of ''Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal'':\n\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rajeevmasand.com/uncategorized/review-dhan-dhana-dhan-goal-painfully-pointless/|title=Review: Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal\u2026 painfully pointless {{!}} Rajeev Masand \u2013 movies that matter : from bollywood, hollywood and everywhere else|website=www.rajeevmasand.com|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/nov/23goal.htm|title=Goal: The Rediff Review|website=www.rediff.com|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/dhan-dhana-dhan-goal/243134/0|title=Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal - Indian Express|website=archive.indianexpress.com|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/dhan-dhana-dhan-goal/236217|title=Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal|last=Joshi|first=Namrata|date=10 December 2007|website=Outlook India|url-status=live |access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes