i/2019/apr/12/nbspthe-tashkent-files-review-a-tacky-thriller-that-feels-longer-than-the-cold-war-11009.html|title=The Tashkent Files review: A tacky thriller that feels longer than the Cold War|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-04-26}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/the-tashkent-files-review-film-by-vivek-agnihotri-doesnt-solve-mystery-shashtri-death|title='The Tashkent Files' \u2013 Prejudiced, Amateurish and Cringe-Worthy|date=2019-04-12|website=The Quint|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>Agnihotri was honoured by the [[Indian Film & Television Directors\u2019 Association]] for the box-office success of the movie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.co.in/vivek-ranjan-agnihotri-honoured-indian-film-television-directors%E2%80%99-association|title=Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri honoured by Indian Film & Television Directors' Association|date=2019-07-10|website=Box Office India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\nAs of {{As of|2020|alt=early 2020}}, Agnihotri is working on ''The Kashmir Files'', a film chronicling the \"unreported history of Kashmiri Hindus\" which is scheduled to be released on 15 August 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-bollywood-turns-to-plight-of-kashmiri-pandits-at-last/346096|title=Bollywood Turns To Plight Of Kashmiri Pandits, At Last|last=|first=|date=|website=Outlook India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/vivek-agnihotri-film-the-kashmir-files-to-release-in-august-2020-not-an-easy-story-to-tell-1580680-2019-08-14|title=Vivek Agnihotri film The Kashmir Files to release in August 2020: Not an easy story to tell|last=MumbaiAugust 14|first=Indo Asian News Service|last2=August 14|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31|last3=Ist|first3=2019 12:47}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/entertainment/after-the-tashkent-files-vivek-agnihotris-next-titled-the-kashmir-files-starring-anupam-kher|title=After 'The Tashkent Files', Vivek Agnihotri's next titled 'The Kashmir Files' starring Anupam Kher|website=Free Press Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref>\n\n==== Short films ====\nAgnihotri's short film ''Mohammad and Urvashi'' won a [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] for best actor in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|last=IANS|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vivek-agnihotri-s-mohammad-and-urvashi-bags-dadasaheb-phalke-award-movie-snippets-117051300491_1.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's 'Mohammad and Urvashi' bags Dadasaheb Phalke award (Movie Snippets)|date=2017-05-13|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> His film was released the following year and he said he received threats for using the name Mohammad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=IANS|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vivek-agnihotri-s-mohammad-and-urvashi-to-release-on-april-24-118041400542_1.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's 'Mohammad and Urvashi' to release on April 24|date=2018-04-14|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/entertainment/vivek-agnihotri-claims-getting-threats-mohammad-urvashi-1502625275.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri claims getting threats over 'Mohammad And Urvashi'|date=2018-04-20|website=The Statesman|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Film certification ===\nIn 2017, Agnihotri was selected as convenor by the [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting (India)|Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]] in the preview committee of [[48th International Film Festival of India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/film/40-member-panel-films-iffi-agnihotri|title=Forty-Member Panel to Curate Films for IFFI With Agnihotri As Convenor|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> The same year, he was selected as member on board of India's [[Central Board of Film Certification]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/entertainment/pahlaj-nihalani-replaced-by-prasoon-joshi-vidya-balan-vivek-agnihotri-in-cbfc-board-meet-all-new-members/804733/|title=Pahlaj Nihalani replaced by Prasoon Joshi: Vidya Balan, Vivek Agnihotri in CBFC Board; meet all new members|date=2017-08-11|website=The Financial Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/latest/846952/pahlaj-nihalani-removed-as-chief-of-central-board-of-film-certification|title=Pahlaj Nihalani removed as chief of Central Board of Film Certification|last=Staff|first=Scroll|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n=== Political activism ===\nAgnihotri has been frequently associated with the [[Right-wing politics|right wing]] and pro-[[BJP]] people by media but he rejects these descriptions and self-identifies as \"India-Wing\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/Neither-left-nor-right/article14244082.ece|title=Neither left, nor right|last=Dundoo|first=Sangeetha Devi|date=2016-04-18|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-11-06|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/releasing-the-tashkent-files-now-public-current-mood-vivek-agnihotri-5642358/|title=Releasing The Tashkent Files now due to public's current mood: Vivek Agnihotri|date=2019-03-25|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/vivekagnihotri/status/906510118136762371?lang=en|title=I have no wing. The only wing I know is 'India wing'. The day left-liberals start talking in favour of India & Indians, I'll support them.|last=Agnihotri|first=Vivek Ranjan|date=2017-09-09|website=@vivekagnihotri|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|last=Agrawal|first=Soniya|date=2018-08-29|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n[[File:Vivek Agnihotri.jpg|thumb|Vivek Agnihotri with his book ''Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam'']]\n\n====''Urban Naxals''====\nIn 2018, Vivek wrote [[Buddha in a Traffic Jam# Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam|''Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam'']],<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/not-easy-to-attract-eyeballs-from-government-vivek-agnihotri-118061500802_1.html |title=Not easy to attract eyeballs from government: Vivek Agnihotri |author=IANS |date=15 June 2018 |work=Business Standard India |access-date=20 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/lifestyle/books/2018/jul/08/vivek-agnihotris-urban-naxals-the-making-of-buddha-in-a-traffic-jam--going-beyond-the-maoist-myth-1838808.html|title=Vivek Agnihotri's Urban Naxals: The Making of Buddha in a Traffic Jam {{!}} Going beyond the Maoist myth|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indictoday.com/reviews/review-urban-naxals-the-making-of-buddha-in-a-traffic-jam-by-vivek-agnihotri/|title=Urban Naxals - The Making of Buddha In A Traffic Jam|date=2018-05-30|website=Indic Today|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref> in which he described individuals in academia and media who were allegedly colluding with [[Naxalite]]s in a bid to overthrow the Indian government and were thus \"invisible enemies of India\" as \"Urban Naxals\".<ref name=\"ThePrint 2018\">{{cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|date=29 August 2018|website=ThePrint|access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> \n\nCritics said the term is \"vague rhetoric\" that is designed to discredit intellectuals who are critical of the establishment and political right and to stifle dissent.<ref name=UNaxals>Coverage and commentary on the term in mainstream media:\n*{{cite web|url=https://theprint.in/politics/hes-making-a-list-of-urban-naxals-but-who-is-vivek-agnihotri/107937/|title=He's making a list of 'Urban Naxals', but who is Vivek Agnihotri?|date=29 August 2018|website=ThePrint|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/swara-bhasker-urban-naxals-1329970-2018-09-02|title=Swara Bhasker on Urban Naxals: You cannot punish people for thinking|language=en|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsclick.in/anti-national-urban-naxal-trajectory-dissent-india|title=From Anti-National to Urban Naxal: The Trajectory of Dissent in India|date=18 September 2018|website=NewsClick|language=en|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/conversations-with-urban-naxals-2-meghnad-everybody-who-does-not-agree-with-vivek-agnihotri-is-an-urban-naxal-5106411.html|title=Conversations with|website=Firstpost|access-date=26 March 2019}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-45294286|title=Why India activist arrests sparked outrage|date=31 August 2018|access-date=26 March 2019|language=en-GB}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.arre.co.in/social-commentary/urban-naxal-uapa-arrests-bhima-koregaon/|title=What Makes An Urban Naxal?|date=29 August 2018|website=Arr\u00e9|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/news/column/a-propaganda-tool-called-urbannaxal/20180713.htm|title=A propaganda tool called #UrbanNaxal|website=Rediff|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Vivashwan|date=5 June 2015|title='Ghoul' and the Spectre of Totalitarianism|url=https://www.epw.in/engage/article/%E2%80%98ghoul%E2%80%99-and-spectre-totalitarianism|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|language=en|volume=53|issue=42}}\n*{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-weekend/just-another-day-in-paradise/article24898900.ece|title=Just another day in paradise|last=Roy|first=Vaishna|date=2018-09-08|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=UNaxalsScholarly>Coverage and commentary on the term in scholarly sources:\n*{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Mohinder|last2=Dasgupta|first2=Rajarshi|date=2 January 2019|title=Exceptionalising democratic dissent: a study of the JNU event and its representations|journal=Postcolonial Studies|volume=22|issue=1|pages=59\u201378|doi=10.1080/13688790.2019.1568169|issn=1368-8790}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Udupa|first=Sahana|date=July 2019|title=Nationalism in the Digital Age : Fun as a Metapractice of Extreme Speech|url=https://ijoc.org/index.php/ijoc/article/view/9105/2715|journal=International Journal of Communication|volume=13|pages=3148|issn=1932-8036}}</ref> Reviews in the [[Organiser (magazine)|Organiser]] and [[The New Indian Express]] had praised the work.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.organiser.org//Encyc/2018/5/28/Urban-Naxals.html|title=Book Review: The Untold Story of Communist Terrorism|website=www.organiser.org|language=en|access-date=23 October 2019}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|Union Minister of Human Resource Development]] [[Smriti Irani]] endorsed Vivek's views of [[Jadavpur University]] and [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] being breeding grounds of \"anti-national elements\" for having refused to screen ''Buddha in a Traffic Jam.''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Singh|first=Vivashwan|date=5 June 2015|title='Ghoul' and the Spectre of Totalitarianism|url=https://www.epw.in/engage/article/%E2%80%98ghoul%E2%80%99-and-spectre-totalitarianism|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|language=en|volume=53|issue=42|pages=7\u20138|via=}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nVivek is married to the Indian actor [[Pallavi Joshi]] and has two children.<ref name=\"ThePrint 2018\" /><ref name=\":3\" />\n\n=== Allegation of sexual harassment ===\nBollywood actor [[Tanushree Dutta]] had accused Vivek of inappropriate behaviour during the filming of [[Chocolate (2005 film)|Chocolate]]. He allegedly asked her to strip and dance to give expression cues to her male co-star [[Irrfan Khan]] during a close-up shot and retreated only after Irrfan and [[Suniel Shetty]] rebuffed him. Vivek had refuted the allegations as \"false and frivolous\", and filed a defamation case against Dutta.<ref name=\"Dutta\">Sources covering the episode:\n\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/tanushree-dutta-alleges-vivek-agnihotri-had-told-her-kapde-utaar-ke-naacho-1351645-2018-09-28|title=Tanushree Dutta alleges Vivek Agnihotri had told her 'kapde utaar ke naacho'|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/tanushree-dutta-accuses-vivek-agnihotri-of-harassment-says-irrfan-suniel-shetty-stood-up-for-her/story-5rFd0z3wycqhIq4LgCuTmI.html|title=Tanushree Dutta accuses Vivek Agnihotri of harassment, says Irrfan, Suniel Shetty stood up for her|date=28 September 2018|website=www.hindustantimes.com|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vivek-agnihotri-refutes-tanushree-dutta-allegations-5385901/|title=Vivek Agnihotri refutes Tanushree Dutta's allegations: Lawyer|date=4 October 2018|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=11 March 2019}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vivek-agnihotri-calls-tanushree-duttas-allegations-false-frivolous/articleshow/66080260.cms|title=Vivek Agnihotri calls Tanushree Dutta's allegations \"false, frivolous\"|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=11 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Starkey|first=Jesse C.|last2=Koerber|first2=Amy|l